The '''[[Cornell Big Red]] men's [[ice hockey]]''' team represents [[Cornell University]], located in [[Ithaca, New York|Ithaca]], [[New York]], in [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]] [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] men's competition. Cornell is one of eight members of the academically prestigious [[Ivy League]] conference and the hockey team plays in the [[ECAC Hockey]] conference.
The 1970 Cornell Hockey team, coached by [[Ned Harkness]] was the first (and currently only team) in [[NCAA]] hockey history to complete a season undefeated and untied with a [[perfect season|perfect]] 29-0-0 record.<ref>http://www.news.cornell.edu/stories/Sept08/HarknessObit.html</ref>
==Overall record== [[File:Cornell'sawesomehockeyteam.jpg|thumb|right|The team saluting fans in Lynah Rink after a game]] *[[Frozen Four|NCAA champions]]: 1967, 1970<ref> {{cite web | title = Cornell Postseason Games | publisher = The Big Red What | url = http://www.tbrw.info | accessdate = 2009-09-13 }} </ref> *NCAA runner-ups: 1969, 1972 *ECAC Champions: 1967, 1968, 1969, 1970, 1973, 1980, 1986, 1996, 1997, 2003, 2005, 2010 *ECAC regular season champions: 1968, 1969, 1970, 1972, 1973, 2002, 2003, 2005 *[[Ivy League]] Champions: 1966, 1967, 1968, 1969, 1970, 1971, 1972, 1973, 1977, 1978, 1983, 1984, 1985, 1996, 1997, 2002, 2003, 2004, 2005 *[[Florida College Hockey Classic|Ned Harkness Cup]]: 2003, 2005, 2008
